# M4-C2: TTF binaries + their OFL license text are fetched at configure time
# by cmake/fetch_fonts.cmake from pinned GitHub release URLs (Inter v4.1 +
# JetBrains Mono 2.304). They are NOT committed — keeps the repo small (the
# ~1.4MB of font data lives only in the build env after first configure, and
# the LICENSE text is regenerated from upstream on every fetch). The generated
# fonts.qrc lives in CMAKE_BINARY_DIR, also not committed.
#
# To force a re-fetch: rm -rf src/resources/fonts/*.ttf src/resources/fonts/LICENSE-*.txt
# && cmake <configure-args>.

*.ttf
LICENSE-Inter.txt
LICENSE-JetBrainsMono.txt
.Inter-*.zip
.inter-extract/
